# MobilityOne Fleet AI

**Enterprise-grade async microservice for fleet management via WhatsApp.**
<br>
*Receives messages · Infers intent via OpenAI · Responds asynchronously via Infobip*

<br>

[![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.11-3776AB?style=for-the-badge&logo=python&logoColor=white)](https://python.org)
[![FastAPI](https://img.shields.io/badge/FastAPI-0.109-009688?style=for-the-badge&logo=fastapi&logoColor=white)](https://fastapi.tiangolo.com)
[![Redis](https://img.shields.io/badge/Redis-7.0-DC382D?style=for-the-badge&logo=redis&logoColor=white)](https://redis.io)
[![Docker](https://img.shields.io/badge/Docker-Ready-2496ED?style=for-the-badge&logo=docker&logoColor=white)](https://docker.com)

</div>

---

## System Architecture

This system uses a non-blocking event loop. The API accepts requests instantly, while heavy lifting (AI processing) happens in the background.

<div align="center">

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[User] -->|WhatsApp| B(API Gateway)
    B -->|Push Task| C[Redis Queue]
    C -->|Pop Task| D[Worker Service]
    D -->|Analyze| E[OpenAI GPT-4]
    D -->|Reply| A
````

\</div\>

## Quick Start

### 1\. Configuration

Create a `.env` file in your root directory.

\<details\>
\<summary\>\<strong\>Click to view .env requirements\</strong\>\</summary\>
<br>

| Variable | Description | Example |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `APP_ENV` | Environment mode | `production` |
| `REDIS_URL` | Redis connection | `redis://redis:6379` |
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | LLM Provider | `sk-...` |
| `INFOBIP_API_KEY` | WhatsApp Provider | `(Your Secret Key)` |

\</details\>

### 2\. Deployment

Run the full stack in detached mode.

```bash
docker-compose up --build -d
```

**Endpoints:**

  * **API Health:** `http://localhost:8000/health`
  * **Webhook:** `POST /webhook/whatsapp`

-----

## Project Structure

| Path | Component | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `routers/webhook.py` | **API Gateway** | Validates HMAC signatures & queues tasks. |
| `services/ai.py` | **Intelligence** | Wraps OpenAI API for intent classification. |
| `services/queue.py` | **Message Broker** | Redis wrapper with exponential backoff. |
| `worker.py` | **Processor** | Background service; handles external API calls. |
| `config.py` | **Config** | Strict Pydantic validation for env vars. |

-----

## Security & Reliability

\<table width="100%"\>
\<tr\>
\<td width="50%"\>

### Security

  * **HMAC-SHA256:** All incoming webhooks are cryptographically verified against `INFOBIP_SECRET_KEY`.
  * **Strict Config:** The app refuses to start if the environment is misconfigured.
  * **No Root:** Docker containers run as a non-privileged user.

\</td\>
\<td width="50%"\>

### Reliability

  * **Async Design:** Webhooks return `200 OK` in \<50ms.
  * **Retry Logic:** Failed deliveries trigger an exponential backoff loop (2s, 4s, 8s...).
  * **Traceability:** Every log entry includes a unique `correlation_id`.

\</td\>
\</tr\>
\</table\>

\<div align="center"\>
<br>
\<sub\>Built for high-throughput production environments.\</sub\>
\</div\>

